consumer: "Consumer app" {
  style.fill: "#fdf2f8"
  style.stroke: "#9d174d"
  shape: person
  "go get github.com/larsartmann/templ-components/icons  (selective!)"
}

consumer -> mod_icons: "imports ONLY what it needs\n(no display/tailwind-merge-go pulled)" {style.stroke: "#9d174d"; style.stroke-width: 2}

gains: |md
  ## What this buys
  - **Selective imports** — `go get .../icons` no longer pulls display/forms/tailwind-merge-go
  - **Enforced boundaries** — `internal/svg` becomes a real module (leakage = compile error)
  - **Independent versioning** — icons/utils can tag v1.x while display is still v0.x
  - **Smaller CI surface** — only changed modules rebuild
  ## What it costs
  - 10 go.mod files to keep in lockstep (automate via tooling)
  - Slightly more consumer friction for cross-package imports
  ## When
  - **Post-v1.0 API freeze** — not before the public API stabilizes
| {near: bottom-right}
